\subsection{Primitive element}
\begin{definition}\label{nf.primitive_element}
\uses{nf,nf.generator}
A primitive element for a {{KNOWL("nf", "number field")}} $K$ is a {{ KNOWL('nf.generator',  'field generator') }} of $K$. In other words, it is an element $\alpha \in K$ such that the inclusion $\Q(\alpha) \subseteq K$ is an equality. The _primitive element theorem_ asserts that every {{KNOWL("nf", "number field")}} admits a primitive element.
\end{definition}


